NAME - program.c

USAGE - 
$ make
$ ./server <input-string>
$ ./client

DESCRIPTION - 
Program which creates two processess and that two processess can communicate with each other by using concept of shared memory.

Example -
# make
gcc -o server server.c
gcc -o client client.c

# ./server "This is Shared Memory Demo."
Shared memory created with id: 163841

# ./client 
Shared memory accessed and id is: 163841
Shared data: This is Shared Memory Demo.
